      "writtenOn": "2016-12-07T18:47:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I still think that this should be const. Even if the SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES structure needs non-const data, since this function doles out the same block of memory every time, I want some guard against accidental modifications. Making it const here, even if we just const_cast it away later, lets it live in a read-only section so we do have that protection.\n\nThe const_cast can go where you stick it into the SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES, since that’s the structure with the problem.\n\nOr have I misunderstood? Does CreateNamedPipe() actually have a need to write to this memory?",
      "revId": "a73482d16dd613440f6550240d90f8d0529d277d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
